first commit

Step 0

Every developer has their own ideas as to the best way to create
top-notch iOS apps. Some developers take advantage of Auto-Layout, some
like to create all of their graphics in code, and some developers even
like to code in Vim!

With the recent release of iOS 7 and Xcode 5, I thought it would be a
great time to provide a case study using a unique set of approaches and
tools to create a basic weather app; you can look upon these as my
recommended iOS 7 best practices. The first stepping-stone to iOS
development used to be building a Todo List app.  However, as iOS has
matured new iOS developers are expected to be proficient in modern
techniques such as data management and consuming web requests.

In this 2-part tutorial series, you’ll explore how to create your own
apps using the following tools and techniques:

 * Cocoapods
 * Manual layout in code
 * ReactiveCocoa
 * OpenWeatherMap

This tutorial is designed for intermediate-level developers who know the
basics, but haven’t moved into too many advanced topics. This tutorial
is also a great start for anyone wanting to explore Functional
Programming in Objective-C.
